caption.text:
1 photo reel ⬇️

This is one of the most SIMPLE instagram reels you will ever create, you only need one photo and instagram will do the rest! Add other photos and location if you choose ⬇️
I’m all about working smarter, not harder.

I’m using vacation photos but any images would work here! 

Here is the step by step guide below:

- go to start a new reel

- Upload any image of your choice 

- Now go to the sparkles filters button and tap the magnifying glass

- Type “Zoom Film” and select the same filter as me

- Your image is now a reel, and you could leave it like this. I think we can improve,

- go to your sticker tab, photo album and add any image to compliment the first, then sticker tab again to add a Polaroid frame.

- Now go to your sticker tab again, add location of where the photo was taken, or a business location you’d like to share. Now anyone that clicks can see where the image was taken.

- go to your sticker tab again, type brown box and add above the frame with any text to suit. 

Be sure to SAVE this post so you don’t forget and let me know if you use this trick!!

Now you have learned about this instagram feature, you might enjoy my 75 minute video lesson, I break down the Instagram app into into simple citizen chunks so you can get the app working for you and your business. Just comment CLASS below and I’ll share a link you can check out!

#socialmediahelp #socialmediamarketing #socialmediagrowth #instagramgrowthtips #reelsideas #reelsinspo #storyidea

caption.text:
I totally get it….

Nobody likes to feel like they’re forcing their business on strangers, you might hate constantly repeating yourself on this app, and you even refrain from posting to not irritate your followers. But the fact is repetition is how the algorithm and your audience understand 

1. Who you are
2. What you offer
3. What they can expect from following you 

In this highly competitive space, you have to keep showing up to remind people what you and your brand are all about…shout it from the rooftops, and be proud of what you have built.

I show up daily, and the overall subject I talk about is always the same! You can learn the same techniques I use in the course I’m currently writing, comment REGISTER below and join the waitlist to be the first to hear when I launch! 

#instagramgrowthstrategy #instagramgrowth #instagramtips #iggrowth #socialmediahelp #contentcreator

caption.text:
How to Share a Reel ⬇️

Instagram has confirmed that reels are the still the no1 way to reach new audiences, but stories are the best way to connect to audiences….well this hack combines both!!

Don’t forget to SAVE this post so you don’t forget the steps!! 

- Go to your reels section, take a screen shot of 3x3 reels covers. Then trim up.

- begin a new story and load the above screenshot, go to sticker tab, click and zoom into digital clock to give a sheer overlay. Now save this image.

- Now go to any reel you’d like to share, tap the airplane button and share to your story. Resize the reel and place on right hand side of the screen.

- Go to your sticker tab, your photo album and add the image you just created, fill the screen with it, then hold down and slide down to bring the reel you shared forwards and send the image back one layer.

- Resize the reel so it fits nicely onto the centre space, go to your sticker tab, type “new reel white”. Place on screen

- Now go sticker tab, type in click, choose your favourite click and place in screen.

Now anyone that clicks that reel gets taken straight through to watch it. 

If you love this instagram reel idea, check out some of my others and make sure you’re following me, I share new ones every single day to help you on your instagram growth journey!

But remember if you want some more detailed help on how to grow your Instagram audience, comment GUIDE below and I’ll send over a link to the strategy I wrote myself which has gained me over 220,000 followers!

reusable_text_info.text: An Instagram Reel, you’ll want to try…

caption.text:
Make a reel in 30 seconds 

Content Doesn’t Need to complicated to create! I LOVE helping and guiding you guys along the way,  try using this audio which is currently trending and a great way to build authority by challenging a belief or busting a myth people might have about your niche.

I’ve given a couple of examples below of text you could use, but always make sure your hook points at your business as the answer to the claim you’re making 

Examples:

“I was so wrong, for so long when I thought I needed to cut out chocolate to lose weight” - personal trainer

“I was so wrong, for so long when I thought wearing jewellery was only for special occasions” - handmade jewellery 

1- SAVE this reel to use same audio
2- in reels section, adjust audio selection in song to same clip as me
3- add 4 second video clip you have of you /your product 
4- add text “I was so wrong, for so long when” (bust a common industry belief)
Examples in Caption 

The course I’m writing is going to be jam packed with content prompts and ideas for you to use on your own Instagram page, comment REGISTER now to join the waitlist and be first to hear when it launches 

#iggrowth #contentcreator #contentstrategy #reelsidea #instagramgrowthtips

caption.text:
New Feature!

You know I like to drop all the latest Instagram updates as they appear, today Instagram rolled out adding music to your profile as a feature to everyone! 

How to find it?

- Go to “Edit profile” from your Profile tab, then tap “Add music to your profile.” 
- Now just search for your favorite song or a song to suit your brand
- Choose which 30 seconds you’d like 
- You can change when it suits you

This is a great way to add personality to your profile or your brand! 

Share with someone who needs to know, and Make sure you’re following me to stay up-to-date with all Instagram latest news and updates! 

Will you use this feature?

caption.text:
✨ 🎙️ 🎧 🎤 ✨⁠ Tune in to our most recent pod episode as we talk to Emma of Embrace Socials, an amazing Instagram Growth Coach, about her journey from model to social media guru.

Emma shares her top tips and tricks for building your social media brand and presence, including how to foster an engaged audience, understanding IG metrics, and so much more!
⁠
Link in bio to listen on Spotify & Apple Podcasts.

caption.text:
Very Demure, Very Mindful!

See how I create short 5 second videos of my day, wherever I am, and use them to promote my business.

This is a reminder, you can do the same, don’t worry if the content doesn’t feel perfect….done is better than perfect! 

Use this audio, add a short clip of you and make sure to add a caption including information on what you do, or the service you provide for your audience or customers! 

For example,

See how I bake every cupcake with love, so you can celebrate your event in style….very demure, very mindful 🧁

See how I deliver this 60 minute massage to transport you into a new state of relaxation…very demure, very mindful 🧘 

Let me know your business below, and maybe we can all give suggestions on how you can be “very demure, very mindful”

#reelidea #contentidea #iggrowth #instagramgrowthtips

caption.text:
Keep your audience watching! 

I’ve always been about working smarter, not harder! Try this idea to increase audience curiosity and watch time whilst they wait and see what the paper reveals!

You can add any announcement you’d like here, use to make a launch or even a call to action asking your audience to comment a specific keyword! 

Such a versatile idea, you can edit the text and audio to suit each time you post!

1. Write any message onto paper and screw up
2. Set your phone up and record yourself doing 2 claps. Without moving your feet, keep the camera rolling and grab the paper you used, with you hands at same position, uncurl the paper to reveal the message
3. Save this video and load into IG, once you have done 2 claps, split the video, and move forward to when you are uncurling the paper.  Go ahead and remove the section of the video where you are reaching for your paper in the middle and you have a simple reel idea to increase audience watch time!

If you liked this idea, make sure you save this post so you don’t forget the steps, and mention GUIDE below to get the link to my growth guide, it’s packed with post ideas, captions to try out and a strategy you can follow!

#instagramgrowth #iggrowth #reelsideas #contentideas

caption.text:
Sharing a Review ⬇️

Reviews are one of the most powerful ways to build trust and credibility with your audience!  They are something I try and do regularly to help me connect with my audience!

Try this tutorial for a fun way to share a review to your instagram account, you can add to your highlights once it’s been posted into your story too. The filter has lots of options and can be used over and over with different reviews on screen!

You’ll want to SAVE this reel so you don’t forget the steps!

- tap and begin a new story, tap camera, create, and slide across to the magnifying glass, type in here “background no966” select the first filter.

- press the shutter button to take a photo of the background to use

- now go to your stickers tab, type review, choose your favourite review sticker and place it on screen.

- Now go to your photo album, where you have screenshot a review to use. Copy and paste the text of the review back into Instagram and paste it on screen on top of the notepad. You can resize to fit and colour to suit theme of your post.

- Now go to your stickers tab, select link, and add the link of your business or brand here in the custom text. Add any text to suit I have used book now and the link on screen.

- Hold your finger down on the link until you see the colour picker, choose a colour on screen to customise the colour of your link sticker.

- Now go to your text tab, and click the A button, to make the text appear that it’s being typed! 

Reviews are great to add to your content strategy, and if you feel you need more ideas on how to grow on instagram, comment GUIDE below & I’ll send the link to my 50 page growth guide.

If you enjoyed this tip, I share new ideas like this every day to help you on your instagram growth journey!

clips_metadata.reusable_text_attribute_string: An Instagram Secret, I bet you didn’t know…

reusable_text_info.text: An Instagram Secret, I bet you didn’t know…

caption.text:
Someone had to say it ⬇️

There is no shortcut to success on Instagram, you have to understand how it works, you have to show up and you have to keep listening and adapting along the way.

You can figure it out in your own, or you can follow my guide, the strategy I used to grow 300,000 followers this year alone. Just comment GUIDE below and I’ll share the link 🫶🏻

My students say:
Your guide provided me with the tools and tips to assist in my business growth. As a newcomer to Instagram, you were able to explain the more complex content in simple terms.

caption.text:
Share if you can relate ↗️

If this is you too? Half way through the summer holidays and I want you to know I see you and I feel you! Ultimately, We are all just trying our best in business all year round!

I know Instagram is just another thing on your ever growing list of jobs to do- but I am here to try and simplify instagram and make it feel manageable and even fun!!

I’m working on a brand new project that’s going to be like having me and my expertise in your pocket. Comment below REGISTER to join the waitlist and be the first to hear about how I can help you every step of the way, and please share this with anyone you know managing that work life balance 🤣

#smallbusiness #smallbusinessuk #instagramarowthexpert #igrowth #instagramgrowthtips #contentcreators

reusable_text_info.text: POV: how it feels running a small business and running a small family

text_info_list.text: POV: how it feels running a small business and running a small family

caption.text:
It’s about time!

Carousel posts can be so so powerful when used correctly, and Instagram have just introduced a way to create them inside the app! No need to use Canva anymore.

Instagram will display both your first screen to your audience and if they don’t engage then they are shown second screen, so you get 2 chances to be seen with each post! 

You can use them to 
- creating connection with your own images and story
- Show step by step tutorials 
- �Tell the story of a review 
- ��Photo dumps if relevant to your page
- ��Educational posts
- ��Before and after to show process

I post daily on my page to keep you informed of new instagram products, tutorial and post ideas and industry news as it happens! If you enjoy what I do, please tag or send to a friend!

I’ll even share 100 captions for you to try if you comment HOOKS below too! 

#contentstrategy #instagramnews #iggrowth #instagramgrowth
